description: This file contains implementation of component functions for a list object in the BSP Engine, including creation, removal, and initialization functions. It interacts with various object types, manages memory, and handles template registration and management within a software system.

methods.name: ANSC_HANDLE BspTemplateListCOCreate(ANSC_HANDLE hContainerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hOwnerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hAnscReserved)
methods.description: Constructs and initializes a new BSP template list object, setting up function pointers for removal and initialization.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS BspTemplateListCORemove(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Destroys the template list object, freeing associated resources, including templates, registered entries, and memory allocations.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS BspTemplateListCOInitialize(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Initializes the list object by setting function pointers for various list operations and creating internal pointer arrays.
